After research, in a hexagonal spiral, the sum of the six neighbors of a number n is always 6n - 6 for n > 1.

For example, see this problem: https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1905225/sum-of-neighbors-in-a-hexagonal-spiral

In that problem, for n=7, sum is 36 = 6*7 - 6

And the neighbors are: 6, 8, 16, 15, 14, 1 — but 6+8+16+15+14+1 = 60, not 36.

